description:
At IMC, data is pivotal in shaping trading decisions across a wide range of financial products. Better data means better decision making and our Data Quality team makes sure we are on top of our data that is used in our trading algorithms. As a member of the Data Quality team, you will play a crucial part in monitoring, identifying, and resolving data issues at scale while we are now in the early stages of forming this team and discipline within IMC globally.



Your core responsibilities:



You will make sure we algorithmically scan terabytes of data to detect potential anomalies and correct them. You will empower our researchers and traders to develop cutting-edge trading strategies based on high-quality data. You will collaborate closely with stakeholders across various areas to understand how data is extracted and utilized, ultimately finding the best ways to improve its quality. How? You will:


* Build and maintain high-quality datasets for use in trading models;
* Monitor data quality and reliability using technical solutions, including machine learning algorithms and advanced analytics, to identify and resolve anomalies;
* Enhance and enrich existing datasets with contextual information;
* Analyze, assess and integrate new data sources for quality and suitability;
* Collaborate with researchers and traders to identify and implement strategies for improving data quality and effectively communicate findings and issues with stakeholders;
* Work with different Tech teams to develop solutions that structurally enhance data integrity across IMC.


What you bring to the team:


* 3-5 years of experience as a Data Analyst/Analytics Engineer working with large datasets;
* A quantitative master’s degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Finance, Econometrics or a related field;
* Interest in Financial Markets and trading (experience is preferred);
* Thorough proficiency in Python and SQL and experience with visualizing data;
* Hands-on experience in manipulating and improving data quality;
* Demonstrated problem-solving and analytical skills;
* Effective stakeholder management skills, with the ability to communicate clearly with technical audiences.


About Us



IMC is a leading trading firm, known worldwide for our advanced, low-latency technology and world-class execution capabilities. Over the past 30 years, we’ve been a stabilizing force in the financial markets – providing the essential liquidity our counterparties depend on. Across offices in the US, Europe, and Asia Pacific, our talented employees are united by our entrepreneurial spirit, exceptional culture, and commitment to giving back. It's a strong foundation that allows us to grow and add new capabilities, year after year. From entering dynamic new markets, to developing a state-of-the-art research environment and diversifying our trading strategies, we dare to imagine what could be and work together to make it happen.

At Medtronic you can begin a life-long career of exploration and innovation, while helping champion healthcare access and equity for all. You’ll lead with purpose, breaking down barriers to innovation in a more connected, compassionate world.
A Day in the Life
As a Sr Business Process Improvement Analyst for EMEA Offer Development, you will be a member of the EMEA Offer Development Management Business Process team within the Global Regions Pricing and Contracting Team. In this team we are focused on customers, employees, patients, and our commitment to the Medtronic mission to alleviate pain, restore health and extend life.
Your main responsibility as a Sr Business Process Improvement Analyst is to aid in integration of our Offer Development Strategy into an end-to-end process with supporting teams and system(s) to ensure interoperability & scalability to maximize value creation. You will collaborate with functional EMEA country leaders and their teams as well as operating units to drive transformation and harmonization of the processes, governance of existing processes, develop playbooks to train teams on new processes, and evolve processes as systems technology evolves to support our journey.
In your daily role, you will be the primary point of contact about the Offer Development and Bid & Proposal Management processes in EMEA. That means you will be responsible for documenting the transformation and later govern and maintain the business processes in a transparent way that will act as a standard for the operating units and Pricing & Contracting. Therefore, you will collaborate with colleagues from countries but also commercial excellence work streams to understand their needs. You will design efficient processes to support business needs and create transparency about existing processes and changes. Furthermore, you will serves as liaison between project management, planning, project team and line management.
You will participate or lead several projects aimed at commercial and operational excellence which are designed to evaluate and ensure the business policies, principles, and standards needs are met. Responsibilities may include the following and other duties may be assigned:* Support the EMEA Offer & Contract Development Transformational Journey. Based on your offer development knowledge, you will be driving change within the organization, setting up or participating in workshops to harmonize, standardize and modernize our Offer & Contract Development Processes in EMEA.
* You will aid in the definition of EMEA specific processes that enable our offer & contract development capabilities such as the implementation of the Configure Price Quote (CPQ) System and ensure this is integrated with other processes and Medtronic systems: Salesforce.com Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system, Vendavo Pricing Management systems and Contract Lifecycle Management (CLM) system like Contract Repository.
* Drive change management of the new CPQ processes for Sales teams and Offer & Contract Development teams by coordinating communications and trainings with specific countries and operating units to enable learning new processes, systems and roles and responsibilities
* Refine and integrate processes for strategic contracting capabilities such as: rebates management, deal analysis and systematic contract composition.

* Proactively govern and maintain the Offer & Contract Development Capability in daily business and support improvement projects from initiation until delivery:
* Partner with the Pricing & Contracting (tendering?) group to understand new initiatives and translate those into harmonized process flows and system capabilities requirements;
* Collaborate with stakeholders to drive change management, process standardization, and ensure they understand the changes that are needed (what, how and when);
* Support cross-functional teams to evaluate, develop and manage projects for key business processes. e.g., IT; SAP team and master data;
* Drive continuous improvement in processes and sharing best practices across the community.


Required Knowledge and Experience:  

* Proven record of accomplishment with leading change within an organization;
* Eagerness to understand the situation of a collaboration partner and to learn about the processes in detail;
* Strong project management and time management skills;
* Ability to develop enterprise end-to-end processes flows leveraging your contacts;
* Expertise in problem solving techniques to efficiently drive process improvements;
* Experience working within a in a project-oriented team;
* Able to communicate effectively to our stakeholders in Business, Pricing, Finance, and IT and able to extract key information needed for KPI driven analytics;
* Experience with the Microsoft Office (Access, Visio, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint);
* Experience in a fast-paced environment
* Knowledge & experience with Agile/SCRUM Methodology
* Ability to develop effective relationships with business user, technical staff, and executive management


