A Transportation Data Analyst monitors and analyzes transportation network performance, identifies opportunities and risks and provides recommendations for action plans to reduce associated risks and improve efficiencies.**Je functie**
--------------


Transportation is an essential and often critical component for the success of organization's supply chain and the business as a whole, making the transportation data analyst an essential role. You will become part of the Transportation team in Benelux within the business unit Contract logistics. It’s a full time position, and applications are welcome from Belgium or Netherlands, as you can be based in one of those countries according to your preference.**Je verantwoordelijkheden**
----------------------------

* Design and implement methods to gather and manage transportation data;
* Research and seek out the most cost-efficient shipment procedures and methods;
* Review and analyze gathered data to locate gaps and opportunity areas in the transportation network and develop methods to improve;
* Monitor transportation spend and measure transportation providers performance and report to management;
* Support Logistics Engineers and Procurement teams with reporting and analytics, including tender and network design analysis;
* Build dashboards, presentations and reporting of transportation related activities, including monthly/quarterly BU reporting;
* Become a Leading user of the Company’s transportation management systems.

**Jouw skills en ervaringen**
-----------------------------

* A completed HBO level/university level degree;
* You are experienced in analyzing and improving supply chain data, information and processes, including a good understanding of all aspects of supply chain processes;
* You have exceptional ability to conceptualize large-picture projects and foresee challenges that need to be addressed;
* You have excellent mathematical and analytical skills, meaning a working knowledge of data analysis and forecasting tools + ability to develop actionable insights from data;
* You have strong working experience with SQL, Power BI or Tableau or similar analytical tools;
* You are a self-driven, multi-tasker, with attention for details, motivated to make a quality impact within the scope of your function;
* Good verbal and written knowledge of English. Another EU language is a plus;
* Available for 32h minimum per week, preference is full time. You have around 3 years of relevant work experience.



